## 14. Build + Test verification (added 2026-06-24)

After all merges completed, ran `dotnet build` + `dotnet test` on the buildable projects (Unity-runtime projects excluded ‚Äî they require Unity DLLs to compile).

### Compound-Spheres (submodule)
- `dotnet build CompoundSpheres/CompoundSpheres.csproj` ‚Üí **0 errors** (250 pre-existing XML-doc warnings on `.csproj`)
- `dotnet build Tests/CompoundSpheres.Tests/CompoundSpheres.Tests.csproj` ‚Üí **0 errors, 0 warnings**
- `dotnet test Tests/CompoundSpheres.Tests/` ‚Üí **19/19 PASS** in 641 ms

### WorldSphereMod (C:)
- `dotnet build tests/WorldSphereMod.Tests.Unit/WorldSphereMod.Tests.Unit.csproj` ‚Üí **0 errors, 0 warnings**
- `dotnet test tests/WorldSphereMod.Tests.Unit/` ‚Üí **157/161 PASS, 3 SKIPPED, 1 FAIL** in 833 ms

### The 1 failure ‚Äî pre-existing, not from merges

`Phase6RigRegistryTests.Constants_defines_the_actor_rig_registry_entries` expects inline `["human"]` syntax in `Constants.cs`. The actual code uses an `AddRigGroup` helper that builds the dict programmatically. All 15 expected IDs (`human`, `dwarf`, `elf`, `orc`, `goblin`, `wolf`, `bear`, `snake`, `butterfly`, `bee`, `bird`, `eagle`, `sand_spider`, `dragon`, `crabzilla`) ARE present in the registry, just not in the test's expected syntactic form. Tracked separately, not introduced by this merge.

### The fix that was needed

`sota/gpu-compute-golive` + `perf/incremental-heightfield` merges added `HeightFieldRenderer.cs` calls to `IGridDimensions.HasDirtyHeights`, `SnapshotDirtyHeights()`, and `TotalTiles`. The interface didn't declare these members ‚Äî `SphereManager` had `HasDirtyHeights` (line 86) and `SnapshotDirtyHeights` (line 415) but no `TotalTiles`, and `GpuSphereManager` had none. Fix:

- `CompoundSpheres/IGridDimensions.cs` ‚Äî added 3 abstract members
- `CompoundSpheres/Gpu/GpuSphereManager.cs` ‚Äî implemented `TotalTiles` (override), `HasDirtyHeights` (false), `SnapshotDirtyHeights()` (empty array ‚Äî GPU path always full-rebuilds)
- `CompoundSpheres/SphereManager.cs` ‚Äî no change (already had the CPU-side impls)

Commit: `75c7f96` (`fix(grid): wire IGridDimensions incremental-heightfield members`).

